No, is not yet fixed.

If you try to create a `IconMenu` with the items from my previous comment the compile will break.

Complete Example

```
import IconButton from 'material-ui/IconButton';
import IconMenu from 'material-ui/IconMenu';
import MenuItem from 'material-ui/MenuItem';
import PersonIcon from 'material-ui/svg-icons/social/person';
import * as React from 'react';

interface IconMenuBugProps {
  someCondition: boolean;
}

class IconMenuBug extends React.Component<IconMenuBugProps> {

  public render() {
    return (
      <IconMenu
        iconButtonElement={<IconButton><PersonIcon color="#AD3489" /></IconButton>}
      >
        <MenuItem value="0" primaryText="Hey" />
        {/* may be false */}
        {!this.props.someCondition &&
          <MenuItem value="1" primaryText="Ho" />
        }
        {/* may be false */}
        {this.props.someCondition &&
          <MenuItem value="2" primaryText="Let's Go" />
        }
      </IconMenu>
    );
  }

}
```

Note that the children array can also contains `false` values other than only `React.ReactElement<MenuItemProps>`

